casebody.data:
UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Pablo Jose NEVAREZ-MARTINEZ, also known as Pablo Jose Nevarez, Defendant-Appellant. No. 07-50880

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 20, 2008. Joseph H. Gay, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Western District of Texas, San Antonio, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Kimberly S. Keller, The Keller Law Firm, San Antonio, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before GARZA, CLEMENT, and SOUTHWICK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Pablo Jose Nevarez-Martinez (Nevarez) has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Nevarez has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
